<body>
	<div id="main">
	<a href="<%= siteURL %>"><img src="<%= url.resolve(siteURL, 'resource/images/logo.png')%>" alt="OpenMRS ID"></a>
	<h2>Your OpenMRS ID (<%= username %>) is ready to use!</h2>
	

<p><%= displayName %>,</p>	

<p>Thanks for signing up for an OpenMRS ID, your key to accessing our online tools and services.</p>

<p>Your OpenMRS ID is fully configured, but you may want to continue by creating a personal space on the OpenMRS Wiki, so we can learn more about you and your interests. Go to <a href="http://wiki.openmrs.org/spaces/createpersonalspace.action">http://wiki.openmrs.org/spaces/createpersonalspace.action</a> to create a personal space.</p>

<p>As a reminder, you can use your OpenMRS ID on the following sites:</p>
<ul>
<li>JIRA (issue tracker): <a href="http://tickets.openmrs.org/">http://tickets.openmrs.org/</a></li>
<li>Confluence (Wiki documentation): <a href="http://wiki.openmrs.org/">http://wiki.openmrs.org/</a></li>
<li>Fisheye (source code): <a href="http://source.openmrs.org/">http://source.openmrs.org/</a></li>
<li>Answers (Q&A): <a href="http://answers.openmrs.org">http://answers.openmrs.org</a></li>
</ul>

<p>To make changes to your OpenMRS ID, log in to the ID Dashboard at <a href="<%= siteURL %>"><%= siteURL %></a>.</p>

<p>In case of problems logging in or signing up, please open a help desk ticket at <a href="http://go.openmrs.org/helpdesk">http://go.openmrs.org/helpdesk</a> &mdash; remember to include your contact information so we can assist you.</p>

<p>Thanks and welcome!</p>
<p>OpenMRS Community Infrastructure Team</p>
	</div>
</body>
</html>